label: sequence mutation
definition: A chemical entity which is the part of a biological sequence that has been changed (by substitution, insertion, and/or deletion) as compared to a reference sequence.

label: nucleotide sequence mutation
definition: A sequence mutation composed of nucleotides.

Subclass axiom: 'variant of' some 'amino acid chain' | ribosomal translation of' some 'nucleotide sequence mutation'
label: amino acid sequence mutation
definition: A sequence mutation composed of amino acids.

label: sequence mutation (symbol)
definition: A sequence datum which encodes a mutation [which is part of a sequence as compared to a reference sequence], represented by a specified notation system.

label: nucleotide sequence mutation (symbol)
definition: A sequence mutation (symbol) that encodes nucleotide mutations.

label: amino acid sequence mutation (symbol)
definition: A sequence mutation (symbol) that encodes amino acid mutations.

label: original variant description
definition: A sequence datum which describes a mutation, written in the user's own notation.
example of usage: C3563S, 12-bp deletion in E at position 54647, D614del, D to G substitution at amino acid 614

label: variant functional effect curation reference document
definition: A document that contains data or statements that a mutation functional description was inferred from by a data curator.

label: protein name
definition: A sequence data which is the name of a protein (typically) assigned by a person and/or according to a naming scheme.
editor note: Planned Obsolescence: this term is a placeholder for a term requested in another ontology. Once the appropriate ontology term is available, this term’s identifier will be obsoleted with a “term replaced by” id of the other term

label: protein symbol
definition: A sequence data which is the short name of a protein typically derived from the protein name.
editor note: Planned Obsolescence: this term is a placeholder for a term requested in another ontology. Once the appropriate ontology term is available, this term’s identifier will be obsoleted with a “term replaced by” id of the other term
